---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is the recommended length for a podcast name?",
    answer: "The recommended length is between 2 and 4 words (under 30 characters). Short, catchy podcast names fit completely on mobile screen player cards and are much easier for listeners to remember and search for."
  },
  {
    question: "Should I include the word 'Podcast' in my show title?",
    answer: "Apple Podcasts and Spotify actually recommend avoiding unnecessary words like 'The Podcast' or 'The Show' if your title is already descriptive. However, adding suffixes like 'Uncut' or 'Daily' can clarify your format."
  },
  {
    question: "Can two podcasts have the exact same name?",
    answer: "Technically yes, RSS feeds allow duplicate show names, but it is highly discouraged. Having a duplicate name creates confusion on Spotify and Apple Podcasts, hurting your search rankings and brand recognition."
  },
  {
    question: "How do I check if my podcast name is available on social media?",
    answer: "Before finalizing your show name, search for the handle on platforms like Instagram, X (Twitter), YouTube, and TikTok to ensure you can secure consistent social media profiles."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I change my podcast show name later?",
    answer: "Yes, you can update your podcast name in your RSS feed host dashboard at any time. However, changing your name after launching can confuse existing subscribers, so choosing a durable name upfront is best."
  }
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Podcast Name Generator - Catchy Show & Audio Titles"
  description="Generate cool, unique, and memorable podcast names. Customize show titles by tech, true crime, mindset, and comedy niches and preview player cards."
  toolName="Podcast Name Generator"
  toolDescription="Create unique, search-compliant podcast show names. Customize by category and preview live Apple Podcasts & Spotify player cards."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Generator Inputs -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <!-- Seed Keyword Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="seed-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 18.75a6 6 0 0 0 6-6v-1.5m-6 7.5a6 6 0 0 1-6-6v-1.5m6 7.5v3.75m-3.75 0h7.5M12 15.75a3 3 0 0 1-3-3V4.5a3 3 0 1 1 6 0v8.25a3 3 0 0 1-3 3Z" />
              </svg>
              Topic or Seed Keyword
            </label>
            <input type="text" id="seed-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. tech, true crime, mindset" value="tech" />
          </div>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem;">
            <!-- Niche Select -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="niche-select" class="icon-label">Podcast Niche</label>
              <select id="niche-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="tech">Tech & Business</option>
                <option value="crime">True Crime & Mystery</option>
                <option value="mindset">Health & Mindset</option>
                <option value="pop">Pop Culture & Comedy</option>
                <option value="arts">Storytelling & Arts</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Suffix Options -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="format-select" class="icon-label">Format Style</label>
              <select id="format-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="clean">Clean (No Suffix)</option>
                <option value="show">With 'Show' or 'Podcast'</option>
                <option value="uncut">With 'Uncut' or 'Daily'</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Actions -->
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn">Generate Names</button>
            <button type="button" id="reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary">Reset Inputs</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Live Mockup Card -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Apple Podcasts / Spotify Show Card Mockup -->
        <div class="podcast-player-card glass" style="background: #121212; color: #ffffff; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 320px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; border: 1px solid #282828; text-align: left; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); font-family: var(--font-body); padding: 1.25rem;">
          <!-- Cover Art and Header Grid -->
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            <!-- Cover Art Thumbnail -->
            <div id="mockup-cover-art" style="width: 72px; height: 72px; border-radius: 12px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1, #a855f7); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: #ffffff; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 800; flex-shrink: 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);">
              TC
            </div>
            <!-- Show Details -->
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; min-width: 0;">
              <span id="mockup-show-title" style="font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 800; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.3; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;">
                The Tech Chronicles
              </span>
              <span style="font-size: 0.72rem; color: #b3b3b3;">Hosted by Creators Feel</span>
              <span style="font-size: 0.68rem; color: #6366f1; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 2px;">⭐ 4.9 (128 ratings)</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Player Controls Bar -->
          <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; border-top: 1px solid #282828; padding-top: 0.85rem;">
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column;">
              <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: #ffffff;">Latest Episode</span>
              <span style="font-size: 0.68rem; color: #b3b3b3;">Ep. 42 • 34 mins</span>
            </div>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 8px;">
              <button type="button" style="background: #1db954; border: none; color: #000000; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800; padding: 8px 14px; border-radius: 20px; cursor: pointer; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;">
                ▶ Play
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generated Results Section -->
    <div id="results-wrapper" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-top: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z" />
        </svg>
        Suggested Podcast Names
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-names-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <button type="button" id="generate-more-btn" class="calc-btn" style="max-width: 200px; padding: 0 1.5rem;">Generate More</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Podcast Name Generator: Craft Memorable Audio & Show Titles</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5;">
        🎙️ <strong>Want to master show naming and audio SEO?</strong> Read our comprehensive <a href="/blog/podcast-name-generator-guide" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">Podcast Show Naming Guide</a> to craft high-recall titles for Spotify and Apple Podcasts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      In audio entertainment and podcasting, your show title represents your brand's primary storefront. When listeners search Spotify, Apple Podcasts, or Amazon Music, your show name is the first item they evaluate alongside your cover art. Building a distinctive, short show name is essential for turning casual listeners into dedicated subscribers. Our free <strong>podcast name generator</strong> helps creators build creative, search-compliant podcast titles that fit platform guidelines automatically.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To craft and audit custom podcast show names in real-time, follow these simple directions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Topic / Keyword:</strong> Enter a base topic, niche, or subject keyword (e.g. tech, crime, mindset).</li>
      <li><strong>Podcast Niche:</strong> Select a show category (Tech & Business, True Crime, Health & Mindset, Pop Culture, or Storytelling).</li>
      <li><strong>Format Style:</strong> Choose a suffix style (Clean, adding 'Podcast'/'Show', or adding 'Uncut'/'Daily').</li>
      <li><strong>Generate List:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Names</strong> to create 15 custom options.</li>
      <li><strong>Preview & Copy:</strong> Click any show name chip to preview it inside the Apple Podcasts & Spotify show player card mockup, and copy it instantly. Click <strong>Generate More</strong> to append 5 more options.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Podcast</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>podcast</strong> is an episodic series of digital audio files that listeners stream or download via RSS feeds on platforms like Apple Podcasts, Spotify, and YouTube Music. Choosing memorable <strong>podcast names</strong> requires balancing search indexing with brand recall. While streaming handles on other platforms can be audited using our <a href="/tools/twitch-username-generator">Twitch Username Generator</a>, audio show titles need to look clean on small mobile player screens. Apple Podcasts recommends keeping titles under 30 characters to prevent unwanted truncation.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator processes your seed terms through customized naming loops:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Niche Keyword Mapping:</strong> Combines your seed topic with high-recall prefixes (like 'Chronicles', 'Uncut', 'Daily', or 'Lab').</li>
      <li><strong>Suffix Formatting:</strong> Appends thematic terms matching tech, crime, or business categories.</li>
      <li><strong>Player Display Checks:</strong> Trims title character sizes to ensure your show name fits cleanly inside player cards.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let's look at how a podcast title length budget is calculated:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Input Seed Name:</strong> `"Tech"`<br />
      <strong>Podcast Niche selected:</strong> `"Tech & Business"`<br />
      <strong>Format Style:</strong> `"With 'Show' or 'Podcast'"`
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Calculation Process:</strong><br />
      ✦ Base prefix: `"The"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>3 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Seed keyword: `"Tech"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>4 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Niche noun: `"Chronicles"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>10 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Format suffix: `"Show"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>4 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Combined output: `"The Tech Chronicles Show"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>24 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Player Display Safe Check: `24 <= 30 characters` (compliant).
    </p>
    <p>
      The generated show title is 24 characters long, which fits cleanly on Spotify and Apple Podcasts player screens without truncation.
    </p>

    <h3>How To Use</h3>
    <p>
      Using our generator is easy. Simply enter your topic, select your preferred podcast niche and suffix styles, and click generate. Clicking any suggested title updates the live player card mockup, allowing you to audit the text layout before copying. If you also publish video versions on YouTube, ensure your episode titles are optimized using our <a href="/tools/youtube-title-length-checker">YouTube Title Length Checker</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This generator is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>New Broadcasters:</strong> Establishing a catchy, memorable show title from day one.</li>
      <li><strong>Business Owners & Brands:</strong> Launching corporate or interview podcasts to build authority.</li>
      <li><strong>Indie Audio Creators:</strong> Naming storytelling, fiction, or true-crime investigative shows.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

